Bolivia: Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever Case in Santa Cruz
-------------------------------------------------
A 43-year-old man was discharged from the Hospital Santa Cruz on 13 Jan
2003 with a dengue hemorrhagic fever diagnosis confirmed with Ig M
seroconversion using Mac EIA test. Both hemorrhagic and hematologic
alterations [had resolved]. A serum sample was sent for serotype
identification.
Dengue virus type 2 (DEN 2) is the oldest serotype circulating in Bolivia,
whereas dengue virus type 1 (DEN 1) was introduced in 1999. Dengue
hemorrhagic fever has appeared this year possibly as a consequence of
introduction of a new strain, maybe dengue virus type 3 (DEN 3). Even now
the outbreak has had a high mortality rate: 2 cases of dengue hemorrhagic
fever have been recorded, one of whom has died.
--
Juan Saavedra Q MD
Internal Medicine and Infectious Diseases
Hospital Santa Cruz
Gabriel Rene Moreno University
<jsquinta@intramed.net.ar>
