Fiji: Dengue Fever Warning for Suva and Western Islands
-------------------------------------------------
Dengue fever, rare in Hawaii but common in the South Pacific, has broken
out in the South Pacific nation of Fiji. Radio Australia reports that a
dengue fever warning has been issued for the Fijian capital of Suva and for
Fiji's western islands. As of Fri 9 Jan 2003, 16 cases have been confirmed
at 2 hospitals.
A dengue fever outbreak on the Hana side of Maui in 2001 led to a statewide
campaign to remove mosquito habitat by throwing out junk that collects
rainwater. Mosquitos breed in standing water that contains organic matter,
such as a spare tire or rain gutter with leaves in it.
